17/*
18 * 1.1.1:
19 * - added support for tiled system memory buffer objects
20 * - added support for NOUVEAU_GETPARAM_GRAPH_UNITS on [nvc0,nve0].
21 * - added support for compressed memory storage types on [nvc0,nve0].
22 * - added support for software methods 0x600,0x644,0x6ac on nvc0
23 * to control registers on the MPs to enable performance counters,
24 * and to control the warp error enable mask (OpenGL requires out of
25 * bounds access to local memory to be silently ignored / return 0).
26 * 1.1.2:
27 * - fixes multiple bugs in flip completion events and timestamping
28 * 1.2.0:
29 * - object api exposed to userspace
30 * - fermi,kepler,maxwell zbc
31 * 1.2.1:
32 * - allow concurrent access to bo's mapped read/write.
33 * 1.2.2:
34 * - add NOUVEAU_GEM_DOMAIN_COHERENT flag
35 * 1.3.0:
36 * - NVIF ABI modified, safe because only (current) users are test
37 * programs that get directly linked with NVKM.
38 * 1.3.1:
39 * - implemented limited ABI16/NVIF interop
40 */

91struct nouveau_cli {
92 struct nvif_client base;
93 struct nvkm_vm *vm; /*XXX*/
94 struct list_head head;
95 struct mutex mutex;
96 void *abi16;
97 struct list_head objects;
98 struct list_head notifys;
99 char name[32];
100 struct drm_device *dev;
101};
102
103static inline struct nouveau_cli *
104nouveau_cli(struct drm_file *fpriv)
105{
106 return fpriv ? fpriv->driver_priv : NULL;
107}

114struct nouveau_drm {
115 struct nouveau_cli client;
116 struct drm_device *dev;
117
118 struct nvif_device device;
119 struct list_head clients;
120
121 struct {
122 struct agp_bridge_data *bridge;
123 u32 base;
124 u32 size;
125 bool cma;
126 } agp;
127
128 /* TTM interface support */
129 struct {
130 struct drm_global_reference mem_global_ref;
131 struct ttm_bo_global_ref bo_global_ref;
132 struct ttm_bo_device bdev;
133 atomic_t validate_sequence;
134 int (*move)(struct nouveau_channel *,
135 struct ttm_buffer_object *,
136 struct ttm_mem_reg *, struct ttm_mem_reg *);
137 struct nouveau_channel *chan;
138 struct nvif_object copy;
139 int mtrr;
140 } ttm;
141
142 /* GEM interface support */
143 struct {
144 u64 vram_available;
145 u64 gart_available;
146 } gem;
147
148 /* synchronisation */
149 void *fence;
150
151 /* context for accelerated drm-internal operations */
152 struct nouveau_channel *cechan;
153 struct nouveau_channel *channel;
154 struct nvkm_gpuobj *notify;
155 struct nouveau_fbdev *fbcon;
156 struct nvif_object nvsw;
157 struct nvif_object ntfy;
158 struct nvif_notify flip;
159
160 /* nv10-nv40 tiling regions */
161 struct {
162 struct nouveau_drm_tile reg[15];
163 spinlock_t lock;
164 } tile;
165
166 /* modesetting */
167 struct nvbios vbios;
168 struct nouveau_display *display;
169 struct backlight_device *backlight;
170
171 /* power management */
172 struct nouveau_hwmon *hwmon;
173 struct nouveau_sysfs *sysfs;
174
175 /* display power reference */
176 bool have_disp_power_ref;
177
178 struct dev_pm_domain vga_pm_domain;
179#ifndef __NetBSD__ /* XXX nouveau hdmi */
180 struct pci_dev *hdmi_device;
181#endif
182};

184static inline struct nouveau_drm *
185nouveau_drm(struct drm_device *dev)

188}

205#define NV_PRINTK(l,c,f,a...) do { \
206 struct nouveau_cli *_cli = (c); \
207 dev_##l(_cli->dev->dev, "%s: "f, _cli->name, ##a); \
208} while(0)
209#define NV_FATAL(drm,f,a...) NV_PRINTK(crit, &(drm)->client, f, ##a)
210#define NV_ERROR(drm,f,a...) NV_PRINTK(err, &(drm)->client, f, ##a)
211#define NV_WARN(drm,f,a...) NV_PRINTK(warn, &(drm)->client, f, ##a)
212#define NV_INFO(drm,f,a...) NV_PRINTK(info, &(drm)->client, f, ##a)
213#define NV_DEBUG(drm,f,a...) do { \
214 if (unlikely(drm_debug & DRM_UT_DRIVER)) \
215 NV_PRINTK(info, &(drm)->client, f, ##a); \
216} while(0)
